From Steve Cunningham Subject Re ACM SIGGRAPH Registration Problem Michael Zyda notes A word of warning for those of you registering for SIGGRAPH ' I just received my registration form back in the mail with the envelope marked Return to sender Moved Left No Address Closed PO Box The address I used to register for SIGGRAPH ' is the one printed on the registration form ACM SIGGRAPH ' PO Box , Chicago, IL I printed the envelope in my best printing, honest but evidently SIGGRAPH ' has skipped town or moved I ended up faxing my registration to I hope that number is real Michael Zyda I had the same problem and called the people who handle the box the problem happened some time ago and was caught almost instantly All registrations going to that address are now fixed See what trouble you get into when you don't procrastinate, Mike And no, SIGGRAPH has not skipped town we're preparing the best SIGGRAPH conference yet Steve Cunningham